article.headline: Bryant 72, Quinnipiac 68
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- Nick Pontes scored 21 points and Adam Parzych added 19 as Bryant defeated Quinnipiac 72-68 in a non-conference game Saturday. The Bulldogs shot 53 percent in the contest and turned the ball over just 11 times. James Feldeine led Quinnipiac with 15 points and Justin Rutty had 13 points and 14 rebounds. It was the second time that Bryant, which joins Quinnipiac in the Northeast Conference next year, had beaten the Bobcats in the season. Quinnipiac led 33-32 at the half, but Bryant went on an 11-3 run to start the second half and never trailed again. Quinnipiac tied the game at 55 with eight minutes to play, but the Bulldogs again responded with a 7-2 run to take a 62-57 lead. The Bobcats cut the deficit to 70-68 with 42 seconds to play, but Andrew Lyell hit two free throws to close out the scoring.
